                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="ScribalSupplication"/>
                           <locus from="48r" to="49r"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                         ወእለ፡ አንበብክምዋ፡ ለዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ኢያንውሩኒ፡ በእንተ፡ ግድፈትየ፡ እስመ፡ እ<supplied reason="omitted">ን</supplied>በለ፡ አብነት፡ ጸሐፍክዋ፡ ወስረዩ፡ ሊተ፡ ወኢትርግሙኒ። 
                              ወጸልዩ፡ 
                                 <sic>ሊቲ፡</sic>
                               በጊዜ፡ ታነብብዋ፡ ወኢትርስኡኒ፡ ፩፡ ፩፡ አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት፡ በጊዜ፡ ጸሎትክሙ፡ ለኃጥእ፡ ወለጊጉይ፡ ወልደ፡ ኃጢአት፡ ዘስምየ፡ ወልደ፡ 
                              ኢየሱስ፡ በፀጋ፡ ጥምቀት፡ ወዘምንኵስና፡ ስምየ፡ ዮሐንስ።
                           </q>
                           <note>The note states that <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11726WaldaIy">Walda ʾIyasus</persName>, whose name as a monk was Yoḥannǝs, was the scribe.</note>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The previous shelfmark <q xml:lang="la">Vat. | aeth. | 51</q> is written on sheet of red leather glued the cover. The number 51 has 
                           been deleted with black ink. The following note is written in Italian on the inner side of the board: <q xml:lang="it">già 51A nella revisione del 
                           luglio 1926 è stato trasportato al numero 103</q>. The note states that the manuscript, previously numbered 51 and 51A, was then numbered as 103.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <locus target="#1r"/>
                           <desc>Previous shelfmark of the manuscript: <q xml:lang="la">N° 51. 
                                    <sic>Aetiopico</sic>
                                 
                              </q>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
